Smart Campus Portal
Project Overview
Smart Campus Portal is a web-based university automation system developed using ASP.NET Web Forms. It provides a centralized platform for students, faculty, and administrators to access campus services based on their roles. The portal simulates course registration, assignment submission, grading, announcements, and fee management.
User Roles
Student Portal
View personal profile and academic records
Register for courses (with prerequisites)
Submit assignments and view grades
Check fee details and payment status
Faculty Portal
Upload course content and assignments
Grade student submissions
Send announcements to students
View attendance reports
Admin Panel
Add or remove students and faculty
Manage courses and offerings
Generate reports (e.g., fee and course registration stats)
Tools & Technologies
Backend: ASP.NET Web Forms, Linq to SQL
Frontend: HTML, CSS, Bootstrap, JavaScript, jQuery
Database: SQL Server (Linq to SQL)
IDE: Visual Studio
Features
Role-based authentication with session management
Fully responsive and mobile-friendly design
CRUD operations for users, courses, assignments, and grades
Dynamic dashboards for each user role
Secure coding practices (input validation, safe queries)
Future Enhancements
Cloud deployment on Azure
Real-time notifications for announcements
Online payment gateway integration
Analytics dashboard for administrators
Mobile application version
Repository Contents
Complete Visual Studio ASP.NET solution folder
All necessary project files to build and run locally
